                <head>229. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Delegations from the United States and the United Kingdom, led by President
                        <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> and Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, respectively, met at
                    Bermuda for a 3-day conference, March 21–23, in order to discuss matters of
                    mutual concern. Extensive documentation on these <pb facs="0571" n="543"
                        xml:id="pg_543"/> talks, which includes discussion of European integration,
                    is scheduled for publication in a forthcoming <hi rend="italic">Foreign
                        Relations</hi> volume.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
